<br>
I imagine the technologically safe way for the gaslight era folks to go about making a large sub orbital rocket would be to develop a reasonably large standard sized solid fuel engine. The herringbone tweed clad gentlemen could then use them in clusters and apply  the staging principal and launch the thing to the edge of space. <br>
